We ordered a frozen margarita and a pina coloda. Nothing crazy, and both were advertised HH specials. It took the bartender about 15 minutes to make the two drinks. At one point he asked a CUSTOMER at the bar "Do you know how to salt a glass?" Seriously? The owner walked over and the drinks were apparently incorrect so he remade them. He salted the rim, but then wiped the excess salt off around the entirety of the rim with his FINGER after he had just been outside potting flowers. So after about 20 minutes we finally got our drinks. They were terrible. The margarita tasted like dirty water. It was weak and tasted awful. The pina colada was made with a mix and tasted like coconut milk - no taste of pineapple or rum. We asked a woman next to us if her drink was any good (a margarita on the rocks served in the wrong glass) and she instantly responded, "No, it was pretty bad." After the first couple sips, we didn't touch our drinks and after HALF AN HOUR of no one acknowledging us, we asked another server to close out our tab. He couldn't do it, and our bartender had left. He left the restaurant and no one else could help us. They had to call him on his cell phone. When he returned he was carrying a bouquet of flowers. When he finally came over to us it had been such an unpleasant experience that we told him our drinks were not great and asked if they could be comped (neither of us has ever sent back a drink before). and if we could order beers instead. "We don't really do that here" he said. And when we asked if it was possible he scolded us. "You guys couldn't have asked me sooner?" he chided, even though he didn't acknowledge us once after giving us our drinks. He did however end up eventually swapping our drinks for beers, which were definitely not ice cold.  This place really needs a bar rescue.
Rude.  Smells like an old shoe store.
Lousy service.  It took them 45 minutes to take the order, and we waited for an hour, and had to walk out. People sitting next to our table also walked out.
Great experience. Service was excellent.

I'm sitting in the restaurant add I write this. We haven't been served a menu or asked for drinks since we were seated 20 minutes ago. The manager is rude and disrespectful to his staff.  Edit 1: We've been served coffee and water after 35 minutes.  Edit 2: 50 minutes, I asked the manager a third time where our food is. He barks at a busy waitress. Five minutes later, our food arrives as if it was cooked in that time. The food was average.  Edit 3: both owners of the restaurant refused to comp our meals.

Breakfast here was pretty good here. Belgium waffles, pancakes, omelets, and hashbrowns were great. Sausage tasted homemade, very good. Service seem pretty was unsatisfactory.  Overall food is good, but please advise for service.

The food is actually pretty good classic American cuisine at affordable prices. They have $3.00 beer specials on all draft and bottled beer and $5.00 margaritas. They also have a nice outdoor area to dine.  The reason I will never go back to this place is due to the worst service I've ever experienced in my life. It wasn't just slow when they weren't busy, our server Daniel was down right hostile and rude. We should have said something to the manager but were too shocked. Not only was general service bad, he complained to our faces about a request to substitute fries on one of the dishes. When he didn't supply condiments I grabbed them myself which he then pulled out of my hands saying "my manager is here I don't want him to see you getting things". He practically tossed our plates onto the table, clearly not caring if we had the right dishes or if we needed anything. All our drinks ran out without an offer for a refill and it was a hassle to split the bill. Many of us have worked in the service industry and know what to expect in good service and where to make exceptions. This guy should not be allowed to work any job related to customer service and he is the sole reason this establishment will not see any more of our business.
Absolutely do not go here, wouldn't serve us couldn't even get water, but had no problem assisting the "white" guests sitting right past us.  Very disturbed that people can be so blatantly rude!

I went to the Woodley Cafe for the Delta Convention, and I was very disappointed to see roaches on the walls, a few mins later a roach went across the table,  I would never go there ago,  the waiter was nice and accomadated us after the situation but the environment was horrible.
Great food, big portions, wonderful family feel. Think you need to go to Open City for a great DC brunch? Think again. Head to Woodley Cafe for less wait and delicious sausage.

The food left much to be desired and the service was horrible (frozen veggies, fish, fries, etc.).  It took over an our to be served and our waiter literally left the restaurant and never came back.  Also, for a party of six they charged automatic gratuity.  Normally I wouldn't mind, but the service was awful!

The service was abysmal.  We were there almost 2 hours and saw the waiter only three times. Took almost 20 mins to even acknowledge we were there and another 5 from there to order our drinks. Food was decent though- except for my friends omelet that came out without any cheese in it.

My boyfriend and I arrived during a breakfast rush and the service seemed quite scrambled. The server arrived and as we waited for her pitch she just stood there and waited for us to say something. I broke the silence and asked for a coffee and my boyfriend proceeded with his order. It was very uncomfortable. Then two other servers back to back come to take our order, but we'd informed them that we had already been helped. Anxious as to how the food was going to be as we were not impressed with the service the people sitting next to us received what looked like an extravagant splay and we sighed relief. Our food came out within a reasonable time frame and it was as easy on the eyes as on the stomach, delicious. Viewing interactions between other customers and their servers I could tell we had the short end. Aside from our particular waitress the experience was quite pleasurable, food was impressive, and priced very reasonably. I'd highly recommend!

Service is terribly slow.  Maybe its timing but sat for 20 mins before getting silverware...have not yet placed drink order.  Considering there were 4 tables before us, doubt anyone will speak to us for another 20 mins.  Only reason I am still here is because the wife insists...God I hope the food is worth this drudgery. Update...another 15 mins and not even a courtesy "sorry"...Leaving and 2 others tables doing the same...

We went here because we didn't want to wait for Open City and decided to find another place for Brunch. BIG MISTAKE. Although we got seated right away it took a long time for our waitress to take our order and a long time for food. The eggs benedict was average, but the hashbrowns actually just tasted like butter (normally I like butter but this was weird and gross). My boyfriend got a breakfast burrito and it was pretty bad. He said the rice was undercooked, and there was almost no salsa or cheese. A couple next to us ordered the Belgian waffles and said they were boring and not very good.  Wait for Open City or find another brunch place!
great for breakfast and sandwiches.

i really liked this place to go for breakfast. we tried to go to places like the diner or tryst but this place was more reasonably priced, you could eat outside, the food was amazing the service is really nice and the best part, no wait!!! and it's still very full and exciting to go for brunch!

On holiday in DC end May, staying in the Shoreham.  Weekend brunch was excellent - not often you get freshly made hollandaise with your eggs Benedict.  More restricted breakfast choice weekdays.  Service was good and friendly; liked the bottomless cup policy and the coffee was excellent.  Much cheaper for breakfast than the hotel!!  Surprised at all the poor reviews from the past.  It's a local cafe and at least met that standard.  Not a dinner venue but ok for breakfast before you go to the zoo.
ok if you like cheddar in your omlet

We waited 20 minutes just for our watered down drinks.  We waited an additional 30 minutes for food.  The food was mediocre at best.  My dressing was watered down. My pasta was supposed to come with bread sticks and didn't. We I asked for bread sticks, I was presented with still partially frozen, freezer hurt rolls. I don't recommend this hole to anyone.

If you like plain burgers and fries with simple soups and salads etc., then this an okay place for you.  The average pricing makes it slightly okay.  The real problem is that with all the other awesome choices in the neighborhood why would you eat here?  It probably a local hangout.  That being said, its not good its not bad.
